                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>\n                                        <date>March 26/54</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>To</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <sic>\n                                                  <addressee>Isaacs Lesser Esqre</addressee>\n                                        </sic>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <placeName>371 Walnut St. Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I arrived in this city from\n                                                  <placeName>Auburn</placeName><lb/> about two weeks\n                                        back, have seen your agent<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr C Myers</persName> who kindly give me the\n                                        Occident<lb/> containing the portion of my letter.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have used my endeavours in forwarding<lb/> your\n                                                  <sic>enterpriseing</sic> work the Bible,\n                                        which<lb/> I must say is a Credit to you, and trust<lb/>\n                                        will prove productive for your labours.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">In regard to further Information<lb/> respecting\n                                        the Jews in <placeName>China</placeName>, I have had an<lb/>\n                                        Interview with <persName>Mr Spear</persName> of whom I spoke\n                                        of<lb/> in my last, he <sic>his</sic> not the Gent who\n                                        was<lb/> in <placeName>China</placeName> in my time, he has\n                                        only been in<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Canton</placeName> three years and not out of it\n                                        till he<lb/> come to this country, as he said to me we\n                                        who<lb/> reside at <placeName>Canton</placeName> can have\n                                        but little com-<lb/>-munication with the Chinese in\n                                        consequence<lb/> of its being unsafe to go out into the\n                                        streets, he<lb/> also says that he never heard or read of\n                                        any such<lb/> sect as Jews &amp;c in\n                                                  <placeName>China</placeName> he is only acquainted\n                                        with<lb/> the Canton Dialect, in the Occident of\n                                                  <date>January</date><lb/> Page 514 you propose to\n                                        send a person duly qualified<lb/> to\n                                                  <placeName>Shanghai</placeName> to open\n                                        communication with<lb/> the people of\n                                                  <placeName>Kai-fong-foo</placeName>, that\n                                        proposition</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3wh2f12s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
