                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3wh2f12s/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to enlighten them more than writing six sheets of<lb/> paper full\n                                        about <placeName>China</placeName>. Questions would\n                                        bring<lb/> things to my memory <sic>wher</sic> other wise I\n                                        cannot<lb/> think of them and I would not have any\n                                        thing<lb/> which I may write or repeat go before the\n                                        public<lb/> but that which I know to be the Truth.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I will conclude by wishing you<lb/> every success\n                                        in your undertakings<lb/> &amp; <sic>Belive</sic> me to be\n                                        yours</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Samuel H. Cohen</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>care of <persName>B Keesing</persName>\n                                        <placeName>Box 488 Post Office</placeName></p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_11_10.pdf\">The\n                                                  above text refers to Occident Volume 11 No. 10\n                                                  pages 510 through 514. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3wh2f12s/canvas/p3"
